he system\nevolves for longer times. I derive both time-dependent and -independent\nequations for the ground state and the time evolution of the PCS ansatz. The\ntime complexity of simulating PCS does not depend on $N$ and is linear in the\nnumber of orbitals in use.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Feb 2015 19:44:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-02-25"}
